Details of the current API:
(The plugin is currently in an early development stage, so the documenation will be improved in the future!)

<ip> -> the ip address of your vdr
<port> -> currently 8002
<format> -> json, html or xml

TIMERS:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/timers.<format>
DELETE http://<ip>:<port>/timers<number>       #the first timer has number 1

RECORDINGS:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/recordings.<format>
DELETE http://<ip>:<port>/recordings<number>	#the first recording has number 1

EVENTS/EPG:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events/<channel>.<format>
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events/<channel>/<duration>.<format>
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events/<channel>/<duration>/<from>.<format>
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events/<channel>/<duration>/<from>.<format>?images=true

<channel> is the number of your channel, the first channel has number 1
<duration> duration of the time period in seconds from which you want to know the event details (optional, default: 3600sec)
<from> start of the time period (optional, default is now)
?images=true will search for epg-images in /var/cache/vdr/epgimages

GET http://<ip>:<port>/events/image/<image_filename>

the image filenames must have the following syntax: <eventid>_<picturenr>{.jpg,.png} or <eventid>{.jpg,.png}

CHANNELS:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/channels.<format>
GET http://<ip>:<port>/channels/<number>.<format>

REMOTE:
PUT http://<ip>:<port>/remote/<key>
possible keys:

             kUp,
             kDown,
             kMenu,
             kOk,
             kBack,
             kLeft,
             kRight,
             kRed,
             kGreen,
             kYellow,
             kBlue,
             k0, k1, k2, k3, k4, k5, k6, k7, k8, k9,
             kInfo,
             kPlay,
             kPause,
             kStop,
             kRecord,
             kFastFwd,
             kFastRew,
             kNext,
             kPrev,
             kPower,
             kChanUp,
             kChanDn,
             kChanPrev,
             kVolUp,
             kVolDn,
             kMute,
             kAudio,
             kSubtitles,
             kSchedule,
             kChannels,
             kTimers,
             kRecordings,
             kSetup,
             kCommands,
             kUser0, kUser1, kUser2, kUser3, kUser4, kUser5, kUser6, kUser7, kUser8, kUser9,
             kNone,
             kKbd
